ly via Go context propagation\n   - Root spans emit a single structured DEBUG log line with the full timing tree on completion\n   - **First instrumentation pass**: all hooks impacting git workflow (PrepareCommitMsg, PostCommit, PrePush) and agent lifecycle (TurnStart, TurnEnd, SessionStart)\n   - Framework should allow drilling down into substeps as time goes on\n   - CLI commands to be instrumented in a future iteration\n   - Package at repo root (`perf/`) for clean import path `github.com/entireio/cli/perf`\n   - Hand-rolled (~300-400 lines), no external dependencies (OpenTelemetry considered overkill)\n   - Plans are NOT version controlled in this repo — don't commit them\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Span-based context-propagated performance measurement (similar to OpenTelemetry spans but lightweight)\n   - Go `context.Context` for automatic span nesting via private context key\n   - `log/slog` structured JSON logging at DEBUG level\n   - Existing `cmd/entire/cli/logging` package integration (`logging.Debug()`)\n   - Flat `steps.<name>_ms` keys in log output for slog compatibility and grep-friendliness\n   - Hook system architecture: hook_registry.go → lifecycle handlers → strategy methods\n   - Manual-commit strategy with shadow branches, condensation, checkpoint system\n   - Subagent-driven development workflow with spec + quality review stages\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`perf/context.go`** (created)\n     - Context propagation for spans using private `contextKey` struct\n     ```go\n     package perf\n     \n     import \"context\"\n     \n     type contextKey struct{}\n     \n     func spanFromContext(ctx context.Context) *Span {\n         if v := ctx.Value(contextKey{}); v != nil {\n             if s, ok := v.(*Span); ok {\n                 return s\n             }\n         }\n         return nil\n     }\n     \n     func contextWithSpan(ctx context.Context, s *Span) context.Context {\n         return context.WithValue(ctx, contextKey{